      • setResourceSpec

        public NamespaceTemplatesTypes.Info.Builder setResourceSpec(com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Structure resourceSpec)
        Resource quotas that this template defines. Quotas on the namespace resources. Refer to NamespaceResourceOptions.get(java.lang.String) for the type of the value for this field. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.00100. If null, no resource constraints are defined in the namespace template.
        Parameters:
        resourceSpec - New value for the property.

      • setNetworks

        public NamespaceTemplatesTypes.Info.Builder setNetworks(java.util.List<java.lang.String> networks)
        vSphere Networks that this template captures and are associated with the namespace after namespace realization. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.00100. This field is null if the cluster hosting this namespace uses NSXT_CONTAINER_PLUGIN or NSXT_VPC as its network provider.
        Parameters:
        networks - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must contain identifiers for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.Network. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will contain identifiers for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.Network.

      • setPermissions

        public NamespaceTemplatesTypes.Info.Builder setPermissions(java.util.List<NamespaceTemplatesTypes.Subject> permissions)
        Permissions associated with namespace template. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.00100. If null, only users with the Administrator role can use this template; for example, this template is applied to the namespace created by self-service-users with the Administrator role.
        Parameters:
        permissions - New value for the property.
